[{"client_msg_id":"b08b2f7f-7c14-4f21-962a-6eef3a83ea60","type":"message","user":"UDDCM376D","text":"むずかしい","ts":"1612868186.018800","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"qzC2"}]},{"client_msg_id":"b744dfed-d27d-4acb-8e22-57e5cae95538","type":"message","user":"UAZ33BKV2","text":"それ自体が動詞になったりするやつならともかく、たしかにそうですね...\nそれとも、普通の(アプリの)スレッドじゃなくて、OSが管理するカーネルスレッド(基本的にそれ自体がプロセス相当)みたいなのがあるから?\nn:m スレッドなのか 1:1 スレッドなのかはあるけど、おしなべてカーネルスレッド=プロセス","ts":"1612861910.018600","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"ChZ"}]},{"client_msg_id":"9b28ce60-6c28-4970-8497-005c8a81a102","type":"message","user":"U01ATUT6PL3","text":"単に thread といってしまうと糸になってしまうからですかね。それにしても明らかに情報科学の文脈でありながら大文字になってるのはちょっとびっくりです","ts":"1612861738.016700","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"CM+q"}]},{"client_msg_id":"11c28fcc-8c39-4754-b8a2-5a0bda20f04d","type":"message","user":"UAZ33BKV2","text":"一般名詞じゃなくて、The Thread(OSでのいわゆる \"Thread\")と表現したいのかな","ts":"1612861351.016000","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"lb5I"}]},{"client_msg_id":"28fda3db-5f7f-40e5-b41a-cbffc0db2f68","type":"message","user":"U01ATUT6PL3","text":"一方で私は \"Thread\" が全部大文字で始まっていることがかなり不思議に感じますね","ts":"1612861278.015300","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"oQ0gs"}]},{"client_msg_id":"20d4746c-23ab-495e-b4e6-16b43b101a24","type":"message","user":"U01ATUT6PL3","text":"よく見たら5時間経ってるな","ts":"1612860052.014800","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"Bxr"}]},{"client_msg_id":"b7c3235f-9578-4942-8b1e-28a3b1de25a0","type":"message","user":"U01ATUT6PL3","text":"OS Scheduler は OS を動作させるさまざまな仕事のうち、「このようなタスク」を達成する仕事を受け持つ、つまり、そうしなければならない、という解釈です","ts":"1612860033.014600","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"UfUxg"}]},{"client_msg_id":"2eed48f3-10d0-4297-b6b5-3989c7082e35","type":"message","user":"U01ATUT6PL3","text":"（既出ですが）これは responsible であることを示す must であると解釈すべきだと思います","ts":"1612859999.013600","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"uWPf6"}]},{"client_msg_id":"ba0e9fb5-cf90-4261-a1c7-0b20dea62b5c","type":"message","user":"UDDCM376D","text":"んー、難しい","ts":"1612838935.012800","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"+eDig"}]},{"client_msg_id":"d328b4c5-5d93-42e5-9ab5-3a124b7e5718","type":"message","user":"U03C6TEAZ","text":"should むずかしいですよね。以前、Rob Pike 氏とやりとりしていて should の意味が分からず SHOULD と大文字で書き直されたのを思い出した。","ts":"1612837487.012100","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"qQQN"}]},{"client_msg_id":"a91cd093-9473-4e13-85e1-d3b1aff7a722","type":"message","user":"UL6CFN8NR","text":"それはたしかに。ブログ記事の翻訳も自然な日本語に越したことはなさそうですね","ts":"1612833224.010900","edited":{"user":"UL6CFN8NR","ts":"1612833232.000000"},"team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"=z79u"}]},{"client_msg_id":"479d15ee-1a54-46c3-91b2-c8879ee85d3a","type":"message","user":"UGJG6S9JM","text":"翻訳ってむづかしいな","ts":"1612833054.010000","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"3A28f"}]},{"client_msg_id":"8aaca388-1948-493b-9242-66c79338e413","type":"message","user":"UGJG6S9JM","text":"RFCとかのは特別な意味があるからそうだけど技術書だと物によっては平易な日本語になったほうが嬉しい気もする","ts":"1612832973.008600","edited":{"user":"UGJG6S9JM","ts":"1612833029.000000"},"team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"lv2Jz"}]},{"client_msg_id":"48A6B026-406A-4C60-A779-98E4A523D7A6","type":"message","user":"UL6CFN8NR","text":"仕様書などの技術系文書は、無理してまで自然な日本語にする必要もないと思います。「しなければならない」と「すべきだ」は混同しちゃダメなやつですし","ts":"1612832822.007100","edited":{"user":"UL6CFN8NR","ts":"1612832949.000000"},"team":"T03C4RC8V","reactions":[{"name":"tashikani","count":1,"users":["UGJG6S9JM"]}],"replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"Zxp"}]},{"client_msg_id":"f995e397-4dcb-4d76-86f0-e350661b30f0","type":"message","user":"UGJG6S9JM","text":"must/should/have toを直訳するとすごい英語から訳された文書だなこれ感が強まる","ts":"1612832708.005600","team":"T03C4RC8V","reactions":[{"name":"sorena","count":2,"users":["UNJ2DANJC","U81LLJ340"]}],"replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"qj5I"}]},{"client_msg_id":"e33e7b16-3e8f-4476-a44a-4b9301881a37","type":"message","user":"UGJG6S9JM","text":"なんだろう、日本語側の能力な気がする、、、","ts":"1612832677.004100","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"b0r"}]},{"client_msg_id":"fadf9980-7192-42ef-9eb1-523c36880f7f","type":"message","user":"UGJG6S9JM","text":"OSのスケジューラーは実行可能なスレッドがあるならコアを暇にさせないようにするべきで、また全ての実行可能なスレッドが同時に実行されているように見せないといけない","ts":"1612832630.003300","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"4Fz0"}]},{"client_msg_id":"9895B54F-12B8-4527-9746-CEF313986B60","type":"message","user":"UL6CFN8NR","text":"なになにする責任がある。そして、なになにもしなければならない。","ts":"1612832601.002800","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"CeVD"}]},{"client_msg_id":"08f7e3fc-9ca6-4a3b-acd8-46ea0213a8fd","type":"message","user":"UGJG6S9JM","text":"ああ、そうかalsoはいってた","ts":"1612832592.002500","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"+cJ"}]},{"client_msg_id":"1D4F2DF0-CBE7-4CEC-93B8-E0E9F1375C89","type":"message","user":"UL6CFN8NR","text":"前の文は「OSスケジューラはなになにする責任がある」になってて、それに対してit alsoで繋がってるので、「しなければならない」でも意味は通じるように思います","ts":"1612832568.002000","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"BTl"}]},{"client_msg_id":"ff9d8b5d-b7fb-400e-a620-d99b66f38b81","type":"message","user":"UGJG6S9JM","text":"的な","ts":"1612832542.001300","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"4Dmn"}]},{"client_msg_id":"7503481d-bfa4-4952-b396-c7536c6a7a30","type":"message","user":"UGJG6S9JM","text":"OSのスケジューラーは実行可能なスレッドがあるならコアを暇にさせないようにするべきで、(もしそれができるなら、)全ての実行可能なスレッドは全部同時に実行されていると言えるに違いない","ts":"1612832541.001100","edited":{"user":"UGJG6S9JM","ts":"1612832561.000000"},"team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"Cian/"}]},{"client_msg_id":"60c75269-a938-4eb6-82ba-278b38261a67","type":"message","user":"UGJG6S9JM","text":"ぜったいそうだよね的な","ts":"1612832470.498900","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"gMP=p"}]},{"client_msg_id":"3707AEB3-D80B-4877-ACA8-6A06B099562D","type":"message","user":"UL6CFN8NR","text":"英語というよりOSのスケジューラの知識が要りそう。もしくはもっと前後の文脈か。","ts":"1612832464.498600","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"yYN0x"}]},{"client_msg_id":"9637a6ac-6ea8-4761-a10e-cc3cad508506","type":"message","user":"UGJG6S9JM","text":"そうに違いない、的な感じでは。","ts":"1612832428.497400","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"FM7"}]},{"client_msg_id":"f4bddaeb-eb50-49ce-a98e-d57a7753f481","type":"message","user":"UDDCM376D","text":"んー、やっぱりmustってよくわからんなぁ\nなんで錯覚させなければいけないって言っているのかがわからない","ts":"1612827841.497100","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"GPI"}]},{"client_msg_id":"613176cb-13bc-4724-964f-6ed4f3fe08f2","type":"message","user":"UDDCM376D","text":"\u0026gt; In the process of creating this illusion, the scheduler needs to run Threads with a higher priority over lower priority Threads.\nこの錯覚を作るには、スケジューラは優先度が低いスレッドよりも高いスレッドを実行する必要がある","ts":"1612827813.496500","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"qx5d"}]},{"client_msg_id":"4c98de74-cdf4-46d1-a070-5745516aafbe","type":"message","user":"UDDCM376D","text":"\u0026gt; The OS scheduler is responsible for making sure cores are not idle if there are Threads that can be executing. \n\u0026gt; It must also create the illusion that all the Threads that can execute are executing at the same time.\nOSのスケジューラは実行可能なスレッドがある場合コアをidelにさせない義務がある\n実行可能なすべてのスレッドを同時に実行していると錯覚させなければ行けない","ts":"1612827746.495700","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"xP+9J"}]},{"client_msg_id":"d09ca759-3d58-44f9-9080-552461198a53","type":"message","user":"UDDCM376D","text":"「実行可能なすべてのスレッドを同時に実行していると錯覚させなければ行けない」で良いのかも","ts":"1612827640.494700","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"md8UD"}]},{"client_msg_id":"420c8e9c-c578-40cb-9d98-9f9ccc430914","type":"message","user":"UDDCM376D","text":"あー、違うな","ts":"1612827615.494100","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"ok7"}]},{"client_msg_id":"e0087456-e933-40df-b681-da78cf6f8d27","type":"message","user":"UDDCM376D","text":"\u0026gt; It must also create the illusion that all the Threads that can execute are executing at the same time.\nここのmustってどういう意味なんでしょうか…\n↑を自分なりに訳すと「それは実行可能なすべてのスレッドを同時に実行しているという錯覚を作るに違いない」で理解ですが、なんか違う気もします","ts":"1612827396.493900","team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"2HXUL"}]},{"client_msg_id":"de3bc1b3-bce7-4ddf-9dbd-67f8231c43d1","type":"message","user":"UDDCM376D","text":"\u003chttps://www.ardanlabs.com/blog/2018/08/scheduling-in-go-part1.html\u003e\nこちらを翻訳しているけど…","ts":"1612827239.491600","attachments":[{"fallback":"Scheduling In Go : Part I - OS Scheduler","id":1,"title":"Scheduling In Go : Part I - OS Scheduler","title_link":"https://www.ardanlabs.com/blog/2018/08/scheduling-in-go-part1.html","text":"Prelude This is the first post in a three part series that will provide an understanding of the mechanics and semantics behind the scheduler in Go. This post focuses on the operating system scheduler. Index of the three part series: 1) Scheduling In Go : Part I - OS Scheduler 2) Scheduling In Go : Part II - Go Scheduler 3) Scheduling In Go : Part III - Concurrency","blocks":null,"service_name":"ardanlabs.com","service_icon":"https://www.ardanlabs.com/favicon.ico","from_url":"https://www.ardanlabs.com/blog/2018/08/scheduling-in-go-part1.html","original_url":"https://www.ardanlabs.com/blog/2018/08/scheduling-in-go-part1.html"}],"team":"T03C4RC8V","replace_original":false,"delete_original":false,"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"rGM"}]}]
